THE ONLY PLACE EITHER.
YOU'D BE SURPRISED.

299
00:18:59,616 --> 00:19:01,917
PLACES UPSTATE
YOU CAN'T DANCE.

300
00:19:01,985 --> 00:19:05,654
PLACES IN KANSAS AND ARKANSAS.
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

301
00:19:05,722 --> 00:19:08,358
MY COUSIN LIVES IN MONTANA,
AND YOU CAN'T DANCE
WHERE SHE LIVES EITHER.

302
00:19:08,425 --> 00:19:10,726
YEAH? SHE EVER
GET BUSTED FOR BOPPIN'?

303
00:19:10,794 --> 00:19:12,862
I DON'T KNOW.
NEVER ASKED HER.

304
00:19:14,731 --> 00:19:16,665
YOU RICH?

305
00:19:16,733 --> 00:19:18,734
NO. NO, WHY?
[Engine Starts]

306
00:19:18,802 --> 00:19:21,170
♪ [Radio: Rock]
I DON'T THINK I EVER
BOUGHT A TAPE BEFORE.

307
00:19:21,238 --> 00:19:23,572
GET SERIOUS.

308
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:26,876
THIS PLACE IS TOO WEIRD.
DON'T YOU EVER LISTEN
TO THE RADIO?

309
00:19:26,944 --> 00:19:29,478
NO. WE GOT ONE RADIO
AT HOME, BUT IT'S NEVER ON.

310
00:19:29,546 --> 00:19:31,714
YOU LIKE MEN AT WORK?
WHICH MEN?

311
00:19:31,782 --> 00:19:33,465
<i>MEN AT WORK.
WHERE DO THEY WORK?</i>

312
00:19:33,534 --> 00:19:36,435
<i>NO, THEY DON'T.
THEY'RE A MUSIC GROUP.
WHAT DO THEY CALL THEMSELVES?</i>

313
00:19:36,503 --> 00:19:40,305
OH, NO.
WHAT ABOUT THE POLICE?
WHAT ABOUT 'EM?

314
00:19:40,373 --> 00:19:42,825
HAVE YOU HEARD THEM?
WHAT, IN CONCERT?
NO, BUT I'VE SEEN THEM.

315
00:19:42,893 --> 00:19:44,994
NO, BEHIND YOU.
WHAT?

316
00:19:45,062 --> 00:19:47,680
[Siren Wailing]
[Ren]
OH, SHIT.

317
00:19:55,772 --> 00:19:59,124
