00:21:57,728 --> 00:22:00,229
AND THAT KIND
OF MUSIC'S OKAY?

348
00:22:00,297 --> 00:22:02,398
WELL, IT'S UPLIFTING.

349
00:22:02,466 --> 00:22:05,635
IT DOESN'T CONFUSE
PEOPLE'S MINDS AND BODIES.

350
00:22:08,254 --> 00:22:10,189
I DON'T--

351
00:22:12,826 --> 00:22:14,510
WHAT?

352
00:22:16,513 --> 00:22:18,447
I SEE.

353
00:22:23,686 --> 00:22:25,721
COULD YOU TELL YOUR MOTHER
TO GO ON TO BED?

354
00:22:25,789 --> 00:22:27,790
I STILL HAVE A LOT
OF WORK TO DO HERE.

355
00:22:27,857 --> 00:22:32,929
I WILL.

356
00:22:32,996 --> 00:22:35,298
DADDY?
WHAT IS IT?

357
00:22:41,405 --> 00:22:43,806
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT, HONEY.

358
00:22:46,743 --> 00:22:49,228
[Students Chattering]

359
00:22:49,295 --> 00:22:52,064
HEY, CHUCK! WHOO!
[Boy]
I'LL CATCH YOU LATER.

360
00:22:52,132 --> 00:22:54,400
HERE. GRAB MY BOOKS.

361
00:22:54,467 --> 00:22:56,402
LET ME IN.

362
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:01,473
HOW YOU DOIN'?

363
00:23:01,542 --> 00:23:03,475
[Horn Honks]

364
00:23:05,979 --> 00:23:08,431
HEY, YOU THE NEW KID?

365
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:12,868
<i>I'M TALKIN' TO YOU.</i>

366
00:23:12,936 --> 00:23:14,987
WHERE'D YOUR TIE GO?

367
00:23:16,990 --> 00:23:21,177
