TO YOUR OLD MAN.

1022
01:07:13,287 --> 01:07:15,222
HEY, LOOK. UH--

1023
01:07:17,625 --> 01:07:19,542
MAYBE, UH--

1024
01:07:21,846 --> 01:07:25,348
MAYBE-- MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T TRY
SO HARD TO FORGET YOUR BROTHER.

1025
01:07:27,251 --> 01:07:30,186
OR TRY TO MAKE YOUR FATHER
FORGET HIM, YOU KNOW?

1026
01:07:31,789 --> 01:07:34,290
[Sighs]

1027
01:07:34,358 --> 01:07:37,427
IT'S NOT THAT EASY.
I KNOW, I KNOW.

1028
01:07:39,263 --> 01:07:41,765
DO I STILL GET THE BOX?
HMM?

1029
01:07:41,833 --> 01:07:44,935
[Chuckles]
GIVE ME THE BOX.
COME ON.

1030
01:07:48,773 --> 01:07:50,524
♪ [Music Box]

1031
01:07:59,767 --> 01:08:01,702
THAT'S NICE.

1032
01:08:10,144 --> 01:08:12,579
THINK YOU MIGHT EVER KISS ME?

1033
01:08:45,146 --> 01:08:46,914
♪ [Continues]

1034
01:08:57,975 --> 01:09:00,176
HARVEY AND BERNIE WERE HERE
FOR A LONG TIME.

1035
01:09:00,245 --> 01:09:04,114
MMM. THEY STILL TALKING
ABOUT THAT DANCE?

1036
01:09:04,181 --> 01:09:06,116
YEAH.

1037
01:09:10,154 --> 01:09:12,088
WHAT DID YOU
DECIDE TO DO?

1038
01:09:12,156 --> 01:09:14,090
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

1039
01:09:15,727 --> 01:09:20,230
THAT'S ONE MORE THING
THAT ARIEL'S NOT GONNA
FORGIVE ME FOR, BUT--

1040
01:09:22,082 --> 01:09:25,852
CAN YOU STEP OUT OF THE WAY
LONG ENOUGH TO REALIZE THAT
SHE'S DOING ALL OF THIS FOR YOU?

1041
01:09:25,919 --> 01:09:29,156
ME? NO.
[Chuckles]

1042
01:09:29,223 --> 01:09:31,691
I DON'T SEE THAT.

1043
01:09:31,759 --> 01:09:36,496
I JUST KNOW THAT WHEN KIDS
DANCE TOGETHER, THEY BECOME
SEXUALLY IRRESPONSIBLE.

1044
01:09:36,564 --> 01:09:38,898
I CAN'T TAKE THE CHANCE OF--
[Laughing]

1045
01:09:40,501 --> 01:09:44,504
WELL, WHAT'S SO FUNNY?
[Mutters]

1046
01:09:44,572 --> 01:09:48,474
YOU TALK LIKE THAT'S THE ONLY
THING THAT GETS 'EM EXCITED.

1047
01:09:48,542 --> 01:09:52,829
DON'T YOU REMEMBER WHEN
WE USED TO LOOK AT EACH OTHER
AND GET EXCITED?

1048
01:09:56,100 --> 01:09:58,785
WELL, IT'S JUST
THE SAME WITH THEM.

1049
01:09:58,853 --> 01:10:01,388
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
PUT THEIR EYES OUT.

1050
01:10:03,224 --> 01:10:05,158
NO.

1051
01:10:18,823 --> 01:10:21,758
NONE OF THIS IS GONNA UNDO
ONE STUPID ACCIDENT.

1052
01:10:23,194 --> 01:10:26,196
I'M RESPONSIBLE
FOR THE SPIRITUAL LIFE
OF THIS COMMUNITY.

1053
01:10:28,399 --> 01:10:30,900
SHAW, YOU CAN'T BE A FATHER
TO EVERYBODY.

1054
01:10:31,970 --> 01:10:33,903
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

1055
01:10:37,108 --> 01:10:40,043
I THOUGHT THAT AT LEAST
YOU BELIEVED IN ME.

1056
01:10:51,522 --> 01:10:53,457
I NEVER STOPPED.

1057
01:10:56,494 --> 01:10:59,596
IT'S A TOWN COUNCIL MEETING.
SEE YOU TOMORROW NIGHT.

1058
01:10:59,663 --> 01:11:04,033
ONLY FAIRIES DANCE.
HEY, I'LL LAY YOU FLAT, ARIEL.

1059
01:11:04,101 --> 01:11:07,537
SUPPORT REN MacCORMACK
AT THE COUNCIL MEETING
TOMORROW NIGHT.

1060
01:11:07,605 --> 01:11:09,539
<i>YOU CAN MAKE A DIFFERENCE!</i>

1061
01:11:09,607 --> 01:11:14,344
I'M CALLING TO REMIND YOU
TO COME TO THE TOWN COUNCIL
MEETING TOMORROW NIGHT.

1062
01:11:18,799 --> 01:11:20,734
HI.

1063
01:11:20,801 --> 01:11:22,935
STILL HURT?
MM, NAH.

1064
01:11:23,003 --> 01:11:25,838
GOOD.
NERVOUS?

1065
01:11:25,906 --> 01:11:27,840
NO, UH-UH.

1066
01:11:27,908 --> 01:11:32,245
LOOK, I, UH-- YEAH.

1067
01:11:32,313 --> 01:11:34,347
YEAH, I'M NERVOUS.

1068
01:11:34,415 --> 01:11:37,668
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M GONNA
SAY TO THE COUNCIL.

1069
01:11:37,735 --> 01:11:40,670
THERE'S ONLY THE SEVEN
OF THEM, THOUGH, RIGHT?

1070
01:11:42,373 --> 01:11:44,307
WHO ELSE IS GONNA BE THERE?

1071
01:11:44,375 --> 01:11:46,643
EVERYBODY.
[Sighs]

1072
01:11:46,711 --> 01:11:49,246
TAKE A DEEP BREATH.
YOU READY?

1073
01:11:53,851 --> 01:11:56,018
WHAT IS IT?

1074
01:11:56,086 --> 01:11:58,020
HOLY BIBLE?
[Chuckling]

1075
01:11:59,189 --> 01:12:01,124
WHAT--

1076
01:12:03,461 --> 01:12:05,395
OH, THIS IS GREAT.

1077
01:12:07,598 --> 01:12:09,599
THIS IS GREAT!

1078
01:12:09,667 --> 01:12:13,836
[Mumbles]
HOW DID YOU KNOW
WHERE TO FIND ALL THIS?

1079
01:12:13,904 --> 01:12:15,838
ARE YOU KIDDING?

1080
01:12:19,977 --> 01:12:23,380
[Class Bell Ringing]
COME HERE.
I WANNA TELL YOU SOMETHING.

1081
01:12:23,447 --> 01:12:25,382
THANKS.

1082
01:12:29,153 --> 01:12:31,821
SHH!
[Man Laughing]

1083
01:12:31,889 --> 01:12:33,823
SHH! SHH!

1084
01:12:38,195 --> 01:12:40,130
COME ON!
[Man Belches]

1085
01:12:40,197 --> 01:12:42,132
[Tires Screech]

1086
01:12:42,199 --> 01:12:44,150
[Amy, Sarah Screaming, Crying]

1087
01:12:44,218 --> 01:12:46,920
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

1088
01:12:48,389 --> 01:12:51,925
<i>- OH, MY GOD!
- AMY!
- OH, WHAT IS IT?</i>

1089
01:12:51,992 --> 01:12:55,078
- "BURN IN HELL"?
THIS SAYS "BURN IN HELL."
- LET ME SEE.

1090
01:12:55,146 --> 01:12:56,980
<i>- [Chattering]
- OH, JESUS.</i>

1091
01:12:57,048 --> 01:12:59,266
OH, REN,
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?

1092
01:12:59,333 --> 01:13:02,802
OBVIOUSLY SOMEBODY'S
TRYING TO MAKE A POINT.
DO YOU SEE NOW?

1093
01:13:02,870 --> 01:13:05,872
YOU DON'T GO
WAVIN' YOUR FLAGS AROUND HERE
WITHOUT PEOPLE TAKIN' SHOTS!

1094
01:13:05,940 --> 01:13:08,108
NOW THIS IS NOT
THE FIRST TIME.

1095
01:13:08,175 --> 01:13:09,943
<i>ARE YOU OKAY?
OH. YOU TOO.
MY BUSINESS WAS OFF.</i>

1096
01:13:10,011 --> 01:13:12,379
<i>BUT PEOPLE ARE TAKING
BUSINESS AWAY FROM ME.</i>

1097
01:13:12,446 --> 01:13:16,749
YOUR AUNT'S BEEN GETTING
SOME UGLY PHONE CALLS, AND
TODAY YOUR MOTHER LOST HER JOB.

1098
01:13:16,817 --> 01:13:19,536
<i>WES!
MOM, IS THAT TRUE? WHAT--</i>

1099
01:13:19,604 --> 01:13:23,105
MR. COLLINS THOUGHT
MAYBE I OUGHT TO STAY HOME
AND BE A PROPER MOTHER.

1100
01:13:23,173 --> 01:13:26,109
- AND WHAT DID YOU SAY?
- I TOLD HIM TO SHOVE IT.

1101
01:13:26,177 --> 01:13:29,128
DAMN IT, ETHEL,
THIS IS SERIOUS!
WES, THERE'S OTHER JOBS!

1102
01:13:29,196 --> 01:13:31,364
WHERE?
[Lulu]
SHOULDN'T YOU CALL THE POLICE?

1103
01:13:31,432 --> 01:13:34,634
I DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH GOOD
IT'LL DO. I'LL GET JIM EARLHAUS
OVER HERE.

1104
01:13:34,701 --> 01:13:38,271
WILL YOU STOP?
NOW WILL YOU STOP?

1105
01:13:39,674 --> 01:13:41,608
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
THIS TOWN.

1106
01:13:41,676 --> 01:13:44,210
IT'S LIKE SOMETHING'S
CHOKIN' EVERYBODY,

1107
01:13:44,278 --> 01:13:46,212
ONLY THEY DON'T KNOW
THEY'RE CHOKIN'.

1108
01:13:46,280 --> 01:13:50,032
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.
WHY THIS DANCE IN THIS TOWN?

1109
01:13:51,634 --> 01:13:55,204
IT'S NOT JUST ABOUT A DANCE--
NOT ANYMORE.

1110
01:13:55,272 --> 01:13:57,739
I KNOW.
THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.

1111
01:13:57,807 --> 01:14:00,292
I WATCH YOU. I SEE.

1112
01:14:07,684 --> 01:14:11,586
- YOU'RE NOT GONNA
UNDERSTAND THIS.
- TRY ME.

1113
01:14:17,694 --> 01:14:19,762
[Mutters]

1114
01:14:19,830 --> 01:14:23,732
WHEN DAD FIRST THREATENED
TO LEAVE, I THOUGHT
IT WAS 'CAUSE OF ME.

1115
01:14:23,800 --> 01:14:29,005
<i>I THOUGHT IT WAS SOMETHIN'
THAT I WASN'T DOIN' RIGHT,
YOU KNOW?</i>

1116
01:14:29,072 --> 01:14:32,658
AND I FIGURED THERE WAS
SOMETHIN' THAT I COULD DO...

1117
01:14:32,725 --> 01:14:37,796
TO MAKE IT LIKE IT WAS
AND THAT HE'D WANNA STAY,
YOU KNOW?

1118
01:14:39,266 --> 01:14:42,734
BUT WHEN HE LEFT
JUST LIKE THAT...

1119
01:14:42,802 --> 01:14:47,473
AND I REALIZED THAT
EVERYTHING THAT I'D DONE,
HOPIN' THAT HE'D STAY--

1120
01:14:49,342 --> 01:14:54,713
EVERYTHING I'D DONE--
IT DIDN'T-- IT DIDN'T
MEAN SHIT, YOU KNOW?

1121
01:14:54,781 --> 01:14:56,715
DIDN'T-- DIDN'T MATTER.

1122
01:14:58,452 --> 01:15:01,753
AND I FELT LIKE,
WHAT DIFFERENCE DOES IT MAKE?

1123
01:15:03,823 --> 01:15:07,759
BUT NOW-- NOW...

1124
01:15:07,827 --> 01:15:10,229
I'M THINKIN'...

1125
01:15:10,297 --> 01:15:14,400
I COULD REALLY DO SOMETHIN',
YOU KNOW?

1126
01:15:14,468 --> 01:15:17,536
LIKE I COULD REALLY DO
SOMETHIN' FOR ME THIS TIME.

1127
01:15:17,604 --> 01:15:20,239
YOU KNOW?

1128
01:15:20,307 --> 01:15:23,075
OTHERWISE,
I'M JUST GONNA DISAPPEAR.

1129
01:15:38,909 --> 01:15:41,927
[Chattering]
[Man]
ALL RIGHT, VIRGINIA.

1130
01:15:41,995 --> 01:15:44,563
I GUESS THAT ENDS
THE DISCUSSION ON THIS ISSUE.

1131
01:15:44,631 --> 01:15:48,483
AND SO THE PRICE
OF A DOG LICENSE WILL GO
FROM $3.50 TO $4.50.

1132
01:15:48,551 --> 01:15:51,704
A LICENSED PET IS A HAPPY ONE.

1133
01:15:51,771 --> 01:15:54,273
AND THAT TAKES CARE
OF OLD BUSINESS. BURLINGTON?

1134
01:15:54,340 --> 01:15:58,711
[Clears Throat]
THANK YOU, UH, VIRGINIA.
THAT WAS REAL GOOD.

1135
01:15:58,779 --> 01:16:03,349
<i>ALL RIGHT.
NOW WE CAN CONSIDER, UH,
ANY NEW BUSINESS.</i>

1136
01:16:03,416 --> 01:16:07,168
<i>[Chattering]
[Clears Throat]
WAIT. EXCUSE ME.</i>

1137
01:16:07,236 --> 01:16:11,140
BEFORE WE BEGIN, I JUST WANT
TO REMIND ALL YOU KIDS.

1138
01:16:11,208 --> 01:16:14,793
WE'RE CONDUCTIN'
AN OFFICIAL MEETIN'.

1139
01:16:14,861 --> 01:16:20,148
<i>WE'RE NOT GONNA TOLERATE
ANY DISTURBANCES.</i>

1140
01:16:20,216 --> 01:16:23,569
<i>OKAY. THE FLOOR IS NOW OPEN
FOR ANY NEW BUSINESS.</i>

1141
01:16:23,636 --> 01:16:28,157
MY NAME IS REN MacCORMACK,
AND I WOULD LIKE TO MOVE...

1142
01:16:28,224 --> 01:16:31,276
ON BEHALF OF MOST OF THE SENIOR
CLASS OF BOMONT HIGH SCHOOL...

1143
01:16:31,344 --> 01:16:33,812
THAT THE LAW
AGAINST PUBLIC DANCING...

1144
01:16:33,880 --> 01:16:35,947
WITHIN THE TOWN LIMITS
OF BOMONT BE ABOLISHED.

1145
01:16:36,015 --> 01:16:39,335
[Cheering]

1146
01:16:42,422 --> 01:16:45,157
UH, MR. CHAIRMAN,
COULD I ADDRESS MYSELF TO THIS?

1147
01:16:45,224 --> 01:16:50,028
- YOU BET.
- EVEN IF THIS WAS NOT A LAW,

1148
01:16:50,096 --> 01:16:52,865
WHICH IT IS,

1149
01:16:52,932 --> 01:16:55,233
I'M AFRAID I WOULD HAVE
A LOT OF DIFFICULTY...

1150
01:16:55,301 --> 01:16:57,335
ENDORSING AN ENTERPRISE...

1151
01:16:57,403 --> 01:17:01,623
<i>WHICH IS AS FRAUGHT
WITH GENUINE PERIL...</i>

1152
01:17:01,691 --> 01:17:03,692
AS I BELIEVE THIS ONE TO BE.

1153
01:17:03,760 --> 01:17:07,279
<i>BESIDES THE LIQUOR
AND THE DRUGS...</i>

1154
01:17:07,347 --> 01:17:10,682
<i>WHICH ALWAYS SEEM TO
ACCOMPANY SUCH AN EVENT,</i>

1155
01:17:10,750 --> 01:17:15,154
THE THING THAT DISTRESSES ME
EVEN MORE, REN,

1156
01:17:15,221 --> 01:17:17,789
IS THE SPIRITUAL CORRUPTION...

1157
01:17:17,857 --> 01:17:19,959
<i>THAT CAN BE INVOLVED.</i>

1158
01:17:20,026 --> 01:17:24,029
<i>THESE DANCES
AND THIS KIND OF MUSIC
CAN BE DESTRUCTIVE.</i>

1159
01:17:24,097 --> 01:17:27,916
<i>AND, UH, REN, I'M AFRAID
YOU'RE GONNA FIND...</i>

1160
01:17:27,984 --> 01:17:31,386
THAT MOST OF THE PEOPLE
IN OUR COMMUNITY ARE GONNA AGREE
WITH ME ON THIS.

1161
01:17:31,454 --> 01:17:33,789
I DO.
[Chattering]

1162
01:17:35,826 --> 01:17:39,061
THAT'S ALL I HAVE TO SAY.
I BELIEVE A VOTE IS IN ORDER
ON THE MOTION.

1163
01:17:39,128 --> 01:17:42,732
<i>- ALL THOSE OPPOSED--
- [Ren]
WELL, EXCUSE ME.</i>

1164
01:17:42,799 --> 01:17:46,151
I WOULD JUST LIKE TO SAY
SOMETHING IF I COULD.
[Loud Chattering]

1165
01:17:46,219 --> 01:17:50,589
IT IS OUTRAGEOUS!
IF YOU THINK THAT YOU--
ELEANOR, SIT DOWN.

1166
01:17:55,128 --> 01:17:58,613
I THINK MR. MacCORMACK
HAS A RIGHT TO BE HEARD.

1167
01:17:58,681 --> 01:18:00,883
[Cheering, Whistling]

1168
01:18:05,822 --> 01:18:09,975
WELL, I JUST--
I-I JUST WANTED TO SAY
A FEW WORDS ABOUT THIS MOTION...

1169
01:18:10,043 --> 01:18:12,778
SO THAT Y-YOU WOULDN'T THINK...

1170
01:18:12,846 --> 01:18:16,481
THAT WE WERE ENCOURAGING
DESTRUCTION...

1171
01:18:16,549 --> 01:18:18,684
WITH THIS IDEA.

1172
01:18:20,970 --> 01:18:23,005
"FROM THE OLDEST OF TIMES,

1173
01:18:23,072 --> 01:18:25,340
"PEOPLE DANCED
FOR A NUMBER OF REASONS.

1174
01:18:25,408 --> 01:18:28,460
"THEY DANCED IN PRAYER...

1175
01:18:28,528 --> 01:18:31,663
<i>"OR SO THAT THEIR CROPS
WOULD BE PLENTIFUL...</i>

1176
01:18:31,731 --> 01:18:33,866
"OR SO THEIR HUNT WOULD BE GOOD.

1177
01:18:33,933 --> 01:18:38,821
"AND THEY DANCED
TO STAY PHYSICALLY FIT...

1178
01:18:38,888 --> 01:18:42,624
"AND SHOW
THEIR COMMUNITY SPIRIT.

1179
01:18:42,692 --> 01:18:45,861
AND THEY DANCED...
TO CELEBRATE."

1180
01:18:48,497 --> 01:18:52,634
AND THAT-- THAT IS THE DANCING
THAT WE'RE TALKIN' ABOUT.
[Woman] YEAH.

1181
01:18:52,702 --> 01:18:54,887
AREN'T WE TOLD...

1182
01:18:54,954 --> 01:18:58,873
IN... PSALM 149:

1183
01:19:00,576 --> 01:19:03,445
"PRAISE YE THE LORD.

1184
01:19:03,512 --> 01:19:06,848
"SING UNTO THE LORD...
A NEW SONG.

1185
01:19:08,584 --> 01:19:11,153
LET THEM PRAISE HIS NAME
IN THE DANCE."

1186
01:19:11,221 --> 01:19:14,056
AMEN.
AMEN.

1187
01:19:14,124 --> 01:19:16,391
AND IT WAS KING DAVID--

1188
01:19:16,459 --> 01:19:20,930
KIND DAVID WHO WE READ ABOUT
IN SAMUEL.

1189
01:19:20,997 --> 01:19:25,317
AND-- AND WHAT DID DAVID DO?
WHAT DID DAVID DO?

1190
01:19:25,385 --> 01:19:27,169
<i>WHAT DID DAVID DO?
[Laughter]</i>

1191
01:19:27,237 --> 01:19:30,305
"DAVID DANCED BEFORE THE LORD...

1192
01:19:30,373 --> 01:19:32,508
"WITH ALL HIS MIGHT,

1193
01:19:32,575 --> 01:19:37,730
LEAPING-- LEAPING AND DANCING
BEFORE THE LORD."

1194
01:19:37,797 --> 01:19:40,398
LEAPING AND DANCING.

1195
01:19:47,907 --> 01:19:50,959
ECCLESIASTES ASSURES US...

1196
01:19:52,862 --> 01:19:55,864
THAT THERE IS A TIME
FOR EVERY PURPOSE UNDER HEAVEN--

1197
01:19:58,268 --> 01:20:01,036
A TIME TO LAUGH...

1198
01:20:01,103 --> 01:20:03,038
AND A TIME TO WEEP,

1199
01:20:04,807 --> 01:20:07,842
A TIME TO MOURN...

1200
01:20:07,910 --> 01:20:09,844
<i>AND THERE IS
A TIME TO DANCE.</i>

1201
01:20:22,358 --> 01:20:25,427
AND THERE WAS A TIME
FOR THIS LAW, BUT NOT ANYMORE.

1202
01:20:25,495 --> 01:20:27,929
SEE, THIS IS
OUR TIME TO DANCE.

1203
01:20:27,997 --> 01:20:33,602
IT IS OUR WAY OF--
OF... CELEBRATING LIFE.

1204
01:20:35,972 --> 01:20:38,190
THAT'S THE WAY IT WAS
IN THE BEGINNING.

1205
01:20:39,793 --> 01:20:41,726
IT'S THE WAY
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN.

1206
01:20:43,129 --> 01:20:45,230
IT'S THE WAY
IT SHOULD BE NOW.

1207
01:21:04,750 --> 01:21:08,420
[Andy]
YOU KNOW YOU WERE RAILROADED,
DON'T YA? HUH?

1208
01:21:09,589 --> 01:21:13,759
BOY, WHEN ARE YOU GONNA WAKE UP
AND SMELL THE COFFEE?

1209
01:21:13,826 --> 01:21:17,696
SHAW MOORE WALKED INTO
THAT MEETIN' WITH THEM VOTES
ALREADY IN HIS POCKET.

1210
01:21:17,764 --> 01:21:20,599
YOU DIDN'T HAVE A PRAYER.
BAD PUN, ANDY.

1211
01:21:23,068 --> 01:21:25,870
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO NOW?

1212
01:21:25,938 --> 01:21:28,206
IT'S OVER.

1213
01:21:28,274 --> 01:21:30,309
WHAT IF IT AIN'T?

1214
01:21:30,376 --> 01:21:32,977
WHAT IF YOU HAD YOUR DANCE
IN BAYSON?

1215
01:21:33,045 --> 01:21:36,080
NO. UH-UH. THE WHOLE POINT WAS
TO DO SOMETHIN' HERE IN BOMONT.

1216
01:21:36,148 --> 01:21:38,583
BAYSON'S,
WHAT, 30 MILES AWAY?

1217
01:21:40,019 --> 01:21:42,788
NOT WHERE IT RUNS UP
TO THESE TRACKS, IT AIN'T.

1218
01:21:44,256 --> 01:21:46,191
HUH?

1219
01:21:46,258 --> 01:21:49,495
WELL, I FIGURE IF THE BOMONT
FIRE TRUCKS CAN'T CROSS
THESE TRACKS,

1220
01:21:49,562 --> 01:21:51,497
NEITHER CAN THE LONG ARM
OF THE LAW.

1221
01:21:51,564 --> 01:21:53,899
YEAH, WHAT ABOUT THE LONG ARM
OF REVEREND MOORE?

1222
01:21:53,966 --> 01:21:56,451
REMEMBER HE SAID IF YOU COULD
FIND A WAY TO CONVINCE HIM,

1223
01:21:56,519 --> 01:21:58,687
IT WOULDN'T BE A SPIRITUAL
CORRUPTION, HE'D THINK ABOUT IT.

1224
01:21:58,755 --> 01:22:01,623
SO?
MAKE HIM THINK ABOUT IT.

1225
01:22:07,029 --> 01:22:09,864
[Reverend]
"AND I BEHELD AND HEARD
AN ANGEL...

1226
01:22:09,932 --> 01:22:13,001
"FLYING THROUGH THE MIDST
OF HEAVEN, SAYING...

1227
01:22:13,069 --> 01:22:16,855
"WITH A LOUD VOICE,
'WOE, WOE,

1228
01:22:16,923 --> 01:22:20,625
"WOE TO THE INHABITERS
OF THE EARTH.'

1229
01:22:20,693 --> 01:22:25,563
"AND I SAW A STAR FALL
FROM HEAVEN UNTO THE EARTH...

1230
01:22:25,631 --> 01:22:29,834
"AND THE ANGEL WAS GIVEN
THE KEY...

1231
01:22:29,902 --> 01:22:32,471
"TO THE BOTTOMLESS PIT.

1232
01:22:32,538 --> 01:22:36,992
"AND HE...
OPENED THE BOTTOMLESS PIT,

1233
01:22:37,059 --> 01:22:39,528
"AND THERE AROSE A SMOKE
OUT OF THE PIT,

1234
01:22:39,596 --> 01:22:42,431
"AS THE SMOKE
OF A GREAT FURNACE.

1235
01:22:42,499 --> 01:22:44,533
<i>"AND THE SUN AND THE AIR
WERE DARKENED...</i>

1236
01:22:44,601 --> 01:22:47,369
BY REASON OF THE SMOKE
OF THE PIT."

1237
01:22:50,106 --> 01:22:52,775
- YES?
- I USED TO GET SUCH A KICK...

1238
01:22:52,842 --> 01:22:55,777
OUT OF WATCHING YOU WORK UP
YOUR SERMONS.

1239
01:22:57,814 --> 01:23:01,533
- AND NOW?
- IT'S DIFFERENT.

1240
01:23:01,600 --> 01:23:04,836
<i>I SEE THE STAGE.
I SEE COSTUMES.</i>

1241
01:23:04,904 --> 01:23:07,205
IT'S SHOW BUSINESS,
ISN'T IT?

1242
01:23:09,492 --> 01:23:12,594
WELL,

1243
01:23:12,662 --> 01:23:17,533
IT'S THE ONLY WAY I KNOW TO...
REACH PEOPLE'S EMOTIONS.

1244
01:23:21,454 --> 01:23:24,255
I HAVEN'T HEARD FROM YOU
FOR A WHILE.

1245
01:23:26,158 --> 01:23:28,493
WHEN WAS IT, THURSDAY?

1246
01:23:29,712 --> 01:23:31,780
I WAS ANGRY
AND YOU WERE ANGRY.

1247
01:23:33,282 --> 01:23:35,450
I WAS NOT.
YES, YOU WERE.

1248
01:23:37,703 --> 01:23:41,739
IF YOU WEREN'T, YOU WOULD HAVE
ASKED ME WHAT WAS WRONG.
YOU KNEW.

1249
01:23:41,807 --> 01:23:46,145
ARIEL, I CANNOT
LET THIS DANCE HAPPEN.

1250
01:23:46,212 --> 01:23:48,347
REN MacCORMACK MADE
A LOT OF PEOPLE STOP AND THINK.

1251
01:23:48,414 --> 01:23:51,133
I OBJECT TO THAT KIND OF MUSIC,
AND I THINK YOU KNOW WHY.

1252
01:23:51,201 --> 01:23:53,801
-BECAUSE PEOPLE FORNICATE TO IT.
-I NEVER SAID THAT.

1253
01:23:53,869 --> 01:23:56,972
-THAT'S WHAT YOU TOLD THE BOARD.
-THAT WAS NOT MEANT
FOR YOUR EARS!

1254
01:23:57,040 --> 01:23:59,474
WHEN DO MY EARS GET OLD ENOUGH?
WHEN YOU STOP PROTECTIN' ME!

1255
01:23:59,542 --> 01:24:03,328
- I'M NO SAINT, YOU KNOW.
- IT IS MY DUTY TO LOOK AFTER
THE SPIRITUAL GROWTH OF THIS--

1256
01:24:03,395 --> 01:24:05,631
I'M NOT EVEN A VIRGIN.

1257
01:24:08,134 --> 01:24:10,935
<i>DON'T YOU TALK LIKE THAT
IN HERE!
WHY NOT?</i>

1258
01:24:11,003 --> 01:24:14,089
ISN'T THIS WHERE I'M SUPPOSED
TO CONFESS MY SINS
TO MY PREACHER?

1259
01:24:14,156 --> 01:24:16,608
IN CHURCH!
I ASK TO BE FORGIVEN!

1260
01:24:16,676 --> 01:24:21,496
- AM I? OH, FORGIVE ME
AND DELIVER ME!
- YOU GET OUT OF HERE!

1261
01:24:21,564 --> 01:24:24,850
- [Indistinct]
- THANK HEAVENS YOU'RE HERE.
PEOPLE ARE CALLING.

1262
01:24:24,917 --> 01:24:27,702
<i>THEY'RE THERE
OVER AT THE LIBRARY.</i>

1263
01:24:27,770 --> 01:24:29,971
[Clapping, Chattering]

1264
01:24:31,891 --> 01:24:33,892
ROGER, ELEANOR,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1265
01:24:33,959 --> 01:24:37,929
WE DECIDED THESE BOOKS
ARE INFLUENCES ON OUR CHILDREN
WE JUST DON'T NEED.

1266
01:24:37,997 --> 01:24:41,199
WHOSE AUTHORITY DO YOU HAVE?
YOU AGREED
THIS WAS GARBAGE.

1267
01:24:41,267 --> 01:24:43,835
WAIT. EVERYBODY, LISTEN TO ME!

1268
01:24:43,903 --> 01:24:45,904
[Panting]

1269
01:24:45,972 --> 01:24:49,007
WHEN DID YOU ALL DECIDE
TO SIT IN JUDGEMENT?

1270
01:24:50,276 --> 01:24:52,244
WHO ELECTED ALL OF YOU...

1271
01:24:52,311 --> 01:24:55,247
TO BE THE SAVIORS OF EVERYBODY'S
SOULS IN BOMONT?

1272
01:24:55,314 --> 01:24:58,816
WE HAVE A PERFECT RIGHT
TO DETERMINE WHAT OUR CHILDREN--
ROGER!

1273
01:25:01,137 --> 01:25:04,840
WHEN YOU'VE BURNED ALL OF THESE,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO THEN?

1274
01:25:07,644 --> 01:25:10,078
CHRIS, TAKE THESE OUT OF HERE.

1275
01:25:12,481 --> 01:25:15,717
SATAN IS NOT IN THESE BOOKS.

1276
01:25:15,785 --> 01:25:18,553
HE'S IN HERE!

1277
01:25:18,621 --> 01:25:21,323
HE'S IN YOUR HEARTS.

1278
01:25:21,390 --> 01:25:24,076
GO ON HOME, ALL OF YOU.

1279
01:25:24,143 --> 01:25:26,879
GO AND SIT IN JUDGEMENT
ON YOURSELVES.

1280
01:25:27,981 --> 01:25:31,266
ROGER... GO HOME.

1281
01:25:32,468 --> 01:25:35,737
ELEANOR, COME ON.

1282
01:25:35,805 --> 01:25:38,240
GO HOME NOW.
COME ON. BOTH OF YOU.

1283
01:26:15,377 --> 01:26:18,246
SOMETIMES THINGS
DON'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

1284
01:26:18,314 --> 01:26:23,251
IF YOU COULD EXPLAIN TO ME
ABOUT MY FATHER, MAYBE I COULD
EXPLAIN TO YOU ABOUT YOUR SON.

1285
01:26:24,653 --> 01:26:27,606
BUT IT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY SENSE.

1286
01:26:30,576 --> 01:26:33,328
LOOK. UH, I GOTTA GO.

1287
01:26:35,698 --> 01:26:40,335
LISTEN. I KNOW YOU'RE GONNA
DO WHAT YOU GOTTA DO, BUT...

1288
01:26:40,403 --> 01:26:43,071
THANKS FOR LISTENIN'.

1289
01:26:46,025 --> 01:26:48,860
REN,

1290
01:26:48,928 --> 01:26:50,845
THANK YOU FOR, UH--

1291
01:26:54,384 --> 01:26:57,819
WELL... THANK YOU.

1292
01:27:12,935 --> 01:27:15,953
THAT WAS YOUR FRIEND REN.

1293
01:27:16,022 --> 01:27:19,891
HE CAME HERE TO ASK ME
IF HE COULD TAKE YOU
TO A SENIOR PROM.

1294
01:27:24,513 --> 01:27:27,215
[Sighs]
WELL, I'M RUNNING OUT
OF ANSWERS, ARIEL.

1295
01:27:28,851 --> 01:27:31,219
I KNOW HOW HARD IT IS
FOR YOU.

1296
01:27:33,756 --> 01:27:36,757
I KNOW I'M NOT
MAKING IT EASIER.

1297
01:27:42,198 --> 01:27:46,134
I JUST DON'T KNOW THAT I BELIEVE
IN EVERYTHING YOU BELIEVE IN.

1298
01:27:49,338 --> 01:27:51,272
BUT I BELIEVE IN YOU.

1299
01:28:16,398 --> 01:28:19,034
I'M... STANDING UP HERE...

1300
01:28:19,101 --> 01:28:21,736
BEFORE YOU TODAY...

1301
01:28:24,339 --> 01:28:26,775
WITH A VERY TROUBLED HEART.

1302
01:28:30,980 --> 01:28:33,164
YOU SEE, MY FRIENDS,

1303
01:28:34,900 --> 01:28:38,502
I'VE ALWAYS INSISTED ON...

1304
01:28:38,570 --> 01:28:42,006
TAKING RESPONSIBILITY
FOR YOUR LIVES.

1305
01:28:43,041 --> 01:28:46,277
<i>BUT... I'M REALLY...</i>

1306
01:28:48,063 --> 01:28:50,698
UH, LIKE A FIRST-TIME PARENT...

1307
01:28:50,765 --> 01:28:54,552
<i>WHO MAKES MISTAKES...</i>

1308
01:28:54,620 --> 01:28:58,156
<i>AND... TRIES TO LEARN
FROM THEM.</i>

1309
01:29:01,010 --> 01:29:03,511
AND, LIKE THAT PARENT,

1310
01:29:04,713 --> 01:29:07,815
<i>I FIND MYSELF
AT THAT MOMENT...</i>

1311
01:29:07,883 --> 01:29:10,885
<i>WHEN I HAVE TO DECIDE,</i>

1312
01:29:12,020 --> 01:29:14,889
DO I HOLD ON...

1313
01:29:15,957 --> 01:29:19,860
OR DO I TRUST YOU
TO YOURSELVES,

1314
01:29:19,928 --> 01:29:22,063
TO LET GO...

1315
01:29:22,130 --> 01:29:26,100
<i>AND HOPE
THAT YOU UNDERSTOOD...</i>

1316
01:29:26,167 --> 01:29:28,703
AT LEAST SOME OF MY LESSONS?

1317
01:29:33,975 --> 01:29:36,344
IF WE DON'T START
TRUSTING OUR CHILDREN,

1318
01:29:38,179 --> 01:29:42,450
HOW WILL THEY EVER BECOME...
TRUSTWORTHY?

1319
01:29:46,154 --> 01:29:49,891
I'M TOLD THAT THE SENIOR CLASS
AT THE HIGH SCHOOL
HAS GOT USE...

1320
01:29:49,958 --> 01:29:52,192
<i>OF A WAREHOUSE IN BAYSON...</i>

1321
01:29:52,260 --> 01:29:56,881
<i>FOR THE PURPOSE OF
PUTTING ON A SENIOR DANCE.</i>

1322
01:29:57,966 --> 01:29:59,900
PLEASE...

1323
01:30:01,270 --> 01:30:04,104
JOIN ME TO PRAY...

1324
01:30:04,172 --> 01:30:06,106
TO THE LORD...

1325
01:30:06,174 --> 01:30:08,208
TO GUIDE THEM
IN THEIR ENDEAVORS.

1326
01:30:11,096 --> 01:30:16,067
♪ LOOKIN' INTO YOUR EYES
I KNOW I'M RIGHT ♪

1327
01:30:16,135 --> 01:30:21,388
♪ IF THERE'S ANYTHING WORTH
MY LOVE, IT'S WORTH A FIGHT ♪

1328
01:30:22,775 --> 01:30:25,043
♪ WE ONLY GET ONE CHANCE

1329
01:30:25,110 --> 01:30:28,796
♪ BUT NOTHIN' TIES OUR HANDS

1330
01:30:28,863 --> 01:30:31,815
♪ YOU'RE WHAT I WANT
LISTEN TO ME ♪

1331
01:30:31,884 --> 01:30:35,819
♪ NOTHIN' I WANT'S
OUT OF MY REACH ♪
♪ I'M FREE

1332
01:30:35,887 --> 01:30:40,758
♪ HEAVEN HELPS THE MAN
WHO FIGHTS HIS FEAR ♪

1333
01:30:40,825 --> 01:30:43,311
♪ LOVE'S THE ONLY THING

1334
01:30:43,378 --> 01:30:46,514
♪ THAT KEEPS ME HERE

1335
01:30:46,582 --> 01:30:48,933
♪ I'M FREE
♪ YOU'RE THE REASON

1336
01:30:49,000 --> 01:30:52,636
♪ THAT I'M HANGIN' ON

1337
01:30:52,704 --> 01:30:58,309
♪ MY HEART'S STAYIN'
WHERE MY HEART BELONGS ♪

1338
01:30:58,377 --> 01:31:00,311
♪ I'M FREE

1339
01:31:01,713 --> 01:31:05,232
♪ RUNNIN' AWAY
WILL NEVER MAKE YOU FREE ♪

1340
01:31:07,670 --> 01:31:11,639
♪ AND NOTHIN' WE SIGN
IS ANY KIND OF GUARANTEE ♪

1341
01:31:13,742 --> 01:31:16,477
♪ I WANNA HOLD YOU NOW

1342
01:31:16,544 --> 01:31:19,446
♪ BUT I WON'T HOLD YOU DOWN

1343
01:31:19,515 --> 01:31:22,466
♪ I'M SHAKIN' THE PAST
MAKIN' MY BREAKS ♪

1344
01:31:22,534 --> 01:31:25,669
♪ TAKIN' CONTROL
IF THAT'S WHAT IT TAKES ♪

1345
01:31:25,738 --> 01:31:28,189
♪ I'M FREE
♪ HEAVEN HELPS THE MAN

1346
01:31:28,256 --> 01:31:31,558
♪ WHO FIGHTS HIS FEAR

1347
01:31:31,626 --> 01:31:34,195
♪ LOVE'S THE ONLY THING

1348
01:31:34,262 --> 01:31:37,398
♪ THAT KEEPS ME HERE

1349
01:31:37,466 --> 01:31:39,750
♪ I'M FREE
♪ YOU'RE THE REASON

1350
01:31:39,818 --> 01:31:43,687
♪ THAT I'M HANGIN' ON

1351
01:31:43,755 --> 01:31:46,390
♪ MY HEART'S STAYIN'

1352
01:31:46,458 --> 01:31:48,809
<i>- LIGHTS!
- ♪ WHERE MY HEART BELONGS </i>

1353
01:31:48,877 --> 01:31:52,046
[Cheering]
♪ YOU'RE THE REASON

1354
01:31:52,113 --> 01:31:55,649
♪ THAT I'M HANGIN' ON

1355
01:31:55,717 --> 01:31:58,002
♪ MY HEART'S STAYIN'

1356
01:31:58,070 --> 01:32:01,339
♪ WHERE MY HEART BELONGS

1357
